{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/retinal-detachment/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"5feedef8-4110-529a-bdea-a1d7f1d1a6b1","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 1ae36c3c-e35f-4591-b356-a7f20188d6f6 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 1ae36c3c-e35f-4591-b356-a7f20188d6f6 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 7e760cd8-786b-45a0-82a4-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 616a33fb-7dcb-4f2d-b3b0-a7f20188d6f6 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 616a33fb-7dcb-4f2d-b3b0-a7f20188d6f6 --><!-- begin field 9900feed-b968-49d4-965d-a7f20188d6f6 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 9900feed-b968-49d4-965d-a7f20188d6f6 --><!-- begin field 36d8ec91-03e0-4cff-afc7-a7f20188d6f6 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 36d8ec91-03e0-4cff-afc7-a7f20188d6f6 --><!-- begin field 0c7eb0ef-3bc6-4d43-89ce-a7f20188d6f6 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 0c7eb0ef-3bc6-4d43-89ce-a7f20188d6f6 --><!-- begin field d131ff96-37fe-4221-8022-a7f20188d6f6 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field d131ff96-37fe-4221-8022-a7f20188d6f6 --><!-- begin field c7068394-6e45-4193-aea2-a7f20188d6f6 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field c7068394-6e45-4193-aea2-a7f20188d6f6 --><!-- end item 7e760cd8-786b-45a0-82a4-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"9be2cb0d-8648-5694-a09c-292ca1ced19e","topicId":"e3f75bdf-a207-4239-9931-367d38a9b7d6","topicName":"Retinal detachment","slug":"retinal-detachment","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2019","chapters":[{"id":"842ff08c-c002-50cd-bab2-348ba3e67be0","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"98f29b98-1286-5c16-a606-4cd90cc70465","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"873d5520-2d22-5b9d-bd04-6d9112dc82ee","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"3b54abb3-d415-51e3-996b-1d6e3bcc3d3b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"0aa87cea-a601-54db-9dcb-ec3117e7098a","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"dbe4b4fd-c326-5686-bd9a-71905fc13c76","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"9f38c5e9-5edd-56fa-a740-0d19004a69af","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"5960233a-64c2-5a35-95ea-6a44ae788808","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"e506d9ce-54a0-57f2-b4d1-49bb28e3d283","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":